  <div class="category-info">
    <h2>Understanding Depressants</h2>
    
    <div class="info-sections">
      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>üß† How They Work</h3>
        <p>Most depressants enhance GABA (gamma-aminobutyric acid) activity in the brain - the primary inhibitory neurotransmitter. This results in reduced neural activity, leading to sedation, anxiety relief, and muscle relaxation. Opioids work differently, activating mu-opioid receptors.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>‚ö†ÔøΩEÔøΩECritical Risks</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Respiratory depression:</strong> Can cause breathing to slow or stop entirely</li>
          <li><strong>Physical dependence:</strong> Rapid development, dangerous withdrawal</li>
          <li><strong>Overdose potential:</strong> Especially when combined with other depressants</li>
          <li><strong>Tolerance:</strong> Requires increasing doses for same effect</li>
          <li><strong>Cognitive impairment:</strong> Memory loss, poor judgment, blackouts</li>
          <li><strong>Withdrawal syndrome:</strong> Can be life-threatening without medical supervision</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>üõ°ÔøΩEÔøΩEHarm Reduction</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Never mix depressants:</strong> Alcohol + benzos = death. Opioids + anything = death.</li>
          <li><strong>Start extremely low:</strong> Tolerance varies wildly, especially with opioids</li>
          <li><strong>Have naloxone (Narcan):</strong> Essential for opioid use - it reverses overdoses</li>
          <li><strong>Don't use alone:</strong> Have someone who can call for help if needed</li>
          <li><strong>Avoid daily use:</strong> Physical dependence develops rapidly</li>
          <li><strong>Taper withdrawal:</strong> Never quit benzodiazepines or alcohol cold turkey</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="info-section">
        <h3>‚öïÔ∏ÅEMedical Uses</h3>
        <p>Despite their dangers, depressants have legitimate medical applications: benzodiazepines for anxiety and seizures, opioids for severe pain, anesthetics for surgery. The key is controlled, supervised use for specific medical needs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
